* Iron Raptor hadn't failed in see the expressions in Prowls face as her and 
Iris argued about Donobot and such, knowing for a fact that Prowl would 
probably get the wrong idea about what she had admitted to.
Sure. She's looked up Dinobots file, just to see what she could find out 
about him.
Believe it or not, she was facinated about him. She never had any intended 
feeling or anything. But it's kinda hard not to notice the only other 
velociraptor in the same groupe as you are.
It also just facinated her about how he could seem so emotionless and such.
It made her edgy around him, but she really didn't know him the more she 
thought about it.
But she didn't like Dinobot, not in the way Prowl obviously thought. But she 
really didn't know if she liked him really either, it's hard to when all you 
know about them is what you read in files.

Iron Raptor bumped up against Prowls shoulder for a moment, hearing in his 
voice that he hadn't liked the subject.*

" I don't like him, Prowl. If that's what you're thinking? I just wanted to 
know a bit about him."

IRIS: " Yeah, I guess I can back up that comment. But I never said that you 
liked him to begin with."

* Iron Raptor growled towards Iris*

" Well, you seemed to be leaning towards that direction a little bluntly"

IRIS: " Slag! I couldn't even imagin you two together! To the pit! Just 
imagin the kids out of that coupling!! No. I gotta abmit, even feather head 
here is better for you then that Pred with a bad 'tude!"

* Iron Raptor rolled her optics but couldn't argue. Dinobot was way too mean 
for her to begin with, and she just wondered how Tavatron could manage to be 
round him almost 27 7.
But that wasn't what mattered now, it was the merging which was the main 
subject.
She leaned towards Prowl a bit more before laying her head on his 
shoulder-plate.*

" You should know that you're the only one I could ever want."

* And with that she snuggled her head a bit into his neck, but they had work 
to be done, and eventually get her into her robot mode again.
But she was ready when he was.

Iris never was one for sentiment, almost making a sickening wound as she saw 
the couple.
She sighed*

IRIS: " Anyway...as soon as the code is disabled just let your spark exit 
your chest, then the energy from that should make her spark exit as well, 
and then they should begin to merge. Simple as that.
But you have to be relaxed, Prowl. And you mind has to be concintrated on 
this task. Otherwise you're asking for disaster."
